        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 4:50PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 450 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Cumming, moving
southwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, nickel sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Cumming, Sugar Hill, Matt, Drew, Ducktown, and Coal Mountain.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
